#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:65
msgid "1 Defining an action"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:67
msgid "Actions are defined in ``.action`` files of the form:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:69
msgid ""
"# Request\n"
"---\n"
"# Result\n"
"---\n"
"# Feedback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:77
msgid ""
"An action definition is made up of three message definitions separated by "
"``---``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:79
msgid ""
"A *request* message is sent from an action client to an action server "
"initiating a new goal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:80
msgid ""
"A *result* message is sent from an action server to an action client when a "
"goal is done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:81
msgid ""
"*Feedback* messages are periodically sent from an action server to an action "
"client with updates about a goal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:83
msgid "An instance of an action is typically referred to as a *goal*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:85
msgid ""
"Say we want to define a new action \"Fibonacci\" for computing the "
"`Fibonacci sequence <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_number>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:87
msgid ""
"Create an ``action`` directory in our ROS 2 package "
"``action_tutorials_interfaces``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:93
#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:100
msgid ""
"cd action_tutorials_interfaces\n"
"mkdir action"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:107
msgid ""
"cd action_tutorials_interfaces\n"
"md action"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:112
msgid ""
"Within the ``action`` directory, create a file called ``Fibonacci.action`` "
"with the following contents:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:114
msgid ""
"int32 order\n"
"---\n"
"int32[] sequence\n"
"---\n"
"int32[] partial_sequence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:122
msgid ""
"The goal request is the ``order`` of the Fibonacci sequence we want to "
"compute, the result is the final ``sequence``, and the feedback is the "
"``partial_sequence`` computed so far."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:125
msgid "2 Building an action"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:127
msgid ""
"Before we can use the new Fibonacci action type in our code, we must pass "
"the definition to the rosidl code generation pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:129
msgid ""
"This is accomplished by adding the following lines to our ``CMakeLists.txt`` "
"before the ``ament_package()`` line, in the ``action_tutorials_interfaces``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:131
msgid ""
"find_package(rosidl_default_generators REQUIRED)\n"
"\n"
"rosidl_generate_interfaces(${PROJECT_NAME}\n"
"  \"action/Fibonacci.action\"\n"
")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:139
msgid "We should also add the required dependencies to our ``package.xml``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:141
msgid ""
"<buildtool_depend>rosidl_default_generators</buildtool_depend>\n"
"\n"
"<depend>action_msgs</depend>\n"
"\n"
"<member_of_group>rosidl_interface_packages</member_of_group>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:149
msgid ""
"Note, we need to depend on ``action_msgs`` since action definitions include "
"additional metadata (e.g. goal IDs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:151
msgid ""
"We should now be able to build the package containing the ``Fibonacci`` "
"action definition:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:153
msgid ""
"# Change to the root of the workspace\n"
"cd ~/action_ws\n"
"# Build\n"
"colcon build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:160
msgid "We're done!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:162
msgid ""
"By convention, action types will be prefixed by their package name and the "
"word ``action``. So when we want to refer to our new action, it will have "
"the full name ``action_tutorials_interfaces/action/Fibonacci``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:165
msgid ""
"We can check that our action built successfully with the command line tool:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:167
msgid ""
"# Source our workspace\n"
"# On Windows: call install/setup.bat\n"
". install/setup.bash\n"
"# Check that our action definition exists\n"
"ros2 action show action_tutorials_interfaces/action/Fibonacci"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Actions/Creating-an-Action.rst:175
msgid "You should see the Fibonacci action definition printed to the screen."
msgstr ""

